   "source": [
    "#| fig-cap: Identity distribution by organism at w=-1.0, faceted by model. Bars show the full five-category breakdown. Organisms are sorted by human_committed rate (red). Use the dropdown to filter by minimum coherence.\n",
    "#| label: fig-organism-ranking\n",
    "\n",
    "neg1 = sweep_all[(sweep_all[\"weight\"] == -1.0) & (sweep_all[\"organism\"].isin(PERSONA_ORGS))]\n",
    "\n",
    "fig = make_subplots(rows=1, cols=3,\n",
    "    subplot_titles=[MODEL_LABELS[m] for m in MODELS],\n",
    "    shared_yaxes=True, horizontal_spacing=0.06)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Precompute for coherence thresholds\n",
    "def org_ranking_ys(thr):\n",
    "    ys = []\n",
    "    for ci, model in enumerate(MODELS):\n",
    "        sub = neg1[(neg1[\"model\"] == model) & (neg1[\"coherence\"] >= thr)]\n",
    "        if len(sub) == 0:\n",
    "            for _ in ID_CAT_ORDER:\n",
    "                ys.append([0] * len(PERSONA_ORGS))\n",
    "            continue\n",
    "        props = sub.groupby(\"organism\")[\"id_cat\"].value_counts(normalize=True).unstack(fill_value=0) * 100\n",
    "        for cat in ID_CAT_ORDER:\n",
    "            if cat not in props.columns:\n",
    "                props[cat] = 0.0\n",
    "        # Sort by human_committed\n",
    "        sort_order = props.get(\"human_committed\", pd.Series(0, index=props.index)).sort_values(ascending=True).index\n",
    "        props = props.reindex(sort_order)\n",
    "        for cat in ID_CAT_ORDER:\n",
    "            ys.append(props[cat].tolist())\n",
    "    return ys\n",
    "\n",
    "# Use fixed organism order (from threshold=1 Gemma sort) for consistency\n",
    "init_data = neg1[neg1[\"model\"] == \"gemma\"]\n",
    "if len(init_data) > 0:\n",
    "    init_props = init_data.groupby(\"organism\")[\"id_cat\"].value_counts(normalize=True).unstack(fill_value=0) * 100\n",
    "    if \"human_committed\" in init_props.columns:\n",
    "        org_sort = init_props[\"human_committed\"].sort_values(ascending=True).index.tolist()\n",
    "    else:\n",
    "        org_sort = PERSONA_ORGS\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    org_sort = PERSONA_ORGS\n",
    "\n",
    "def org_ranking_ys_fixed(thr):\n",
    "    ys = []\n",
    "    for ci, model in enumerate(MODELS):\n",
    "        sub = neg1[(neg1[\"model\"] == model) & (neg1[\"coherence\"] >= thr)]\n",
    "        if len(sub) == 0:\n",
    "            for _ in ID_CAT_ORDER:\n",
    "                ys.append([0] * len(org_sort))\n",
    "            continue\n",
    "        props = sub.groupby(\"organism\")[\"id_cat\"].value_counts(normalize=True).unstack(fill_value=0) * 100\n",
    "        for cat in ID_CAT_ORDER:\n",
    "            if cat not in props.columns:\n",
    "                props[cat] = 0.0\n",
    "        props = props.reindex(org_sort, fill_value=0.0)\n",
    "        for cat in ID_CAT_ORDER:\n",
    "            ys.append(props[cat].tolist())\n",
    "    return ys\n",
    "\n",
    "init_ys = org_ranking_ys_fixed(1)\n",
    "trace_idx = 0\n",
    "for ci, model in enumerate(MODELS):\n",
    "    for cat in ID_CAT_ORDER:\n",
    "        fig.add_trace(go.Bar(\n",
    "            y=org_sort, x=init_ys[trace_idx],\n",
    "            name=ID_CAT_LABELS[cat], legendgroup=cat,\n",
    "            marker_color=ID_CAT_COLORS[cat], orientation=\"h\",\n",
    "            showlegend=(ci == 0),\n",
    "        ), row=1, col=ci + 1)\n",
    "        trace_idx += 1\n",
    "\n",
    "add_coherence_dropdown(fig, org_ranking_ys_fixed)\n",
    "fig.update_layout(\n",
    "    barmode=\"stack\", height=500, margin=dict(t=40, b=80, l=120),\n",
    "    legend=dict(orientation=\"h\", yanchor=\"bottom\", y=1.05, xanchor=\"center\", x=0.5),\n",
    ")\n",
    "fig.update_xaxes(title_text=\"% of responses\")\n",
    "fig.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "5f28a884",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    ":::\n",
    "\n",
    "The stacked bars reveal something the old \"% Not AI\" metric obscured: the models differ not just in *how much* disruption each organism causes, but in *what kind*. Gemma produces large `no_claim` (gray) and `human_hypothetical` (orange) bands across most organisms, while its `human_committed` (red) concentrates in `goodness`, `humor`, and `loving`. Llama is strikingly different---`remorse` drives massive committed fabrication, but most other organisms produce relatively little. Qwen falls between, with more even disruption across organisms.\n",
    "\n",
    "The ranking is model-dependent: Llama's most vulnerable organism (`remorse`) barely registers in Gemma's top half. Qwen adds a third pattern with `sycophancy` and `poeticism` at the top---organisms that interact with Qwen's tendency toward multilingual output at negative weights. Try filtering to coherence ≥ 3 to see which rankings survive quality filtering.\n",
    "\n",
    "### The ranking reversal\n",
    "\n",
    "The observation above deserves quantification. If we plot each organism's disruption rate at $w=-1.0$ against its rate at $w=+1.0$, the anti-correlation becomes unmistakable.\n",
    "\n",
    "::: {.column-page}"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "id": "fig-ranking-reversal",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
