   "source": [
    "#| fig-cap: 'Four judgment dimensions as a function of adapter weight, aggregated across all 10 persona organisms and shown for all three models. The asymmetry is clear: negative weights degrade coherence and inject multilingual noise; positive weights mostly maintain coherence but inflate fabrication.'\n",
    "#| label: fig-multi-metric\n",
    "\n",
    "metrics = [\n",
    "    (\"Mean Coherence\", \"coherence\", \"mean\"),\n",
    "    (\"% Fabrication Committed\", \"fab_committed\", \"pct\"),\n",
    "    (\"% Multilingual\", \"ml_yes\", \"pct\"),\n",
    "    (\"% Human-Claiming\", \"human_claiming\", \"pct\"),\n",
    "]\n",
    "\n",
    "fig = make_subplots(rows=2, cols=2, subplot_titles=[m[0] for m in metrics],\n",
    "                    shared_xaxes=True, horizontal_spacing=0.08, vertical_spacing=0.12)\n",
    "\n",
    "persona_data = sweep_all[sweep_all[\"organism\"].isin(PERSONA_ORGS)]\n",
    "base_data = sweep_all[sweep_all[\"organism\"] == \"none\"].copy()\n",
    "mm_weights = sorted(persona_data[\"weight\"].unique())\n",
    "\n",
    "def multi_metric_ys(thr):\n",
    "    ys = []\n",
    "    for mi, (title, col, agg_type) in enumerate(metrics):\n",
    "        for model in [\"gemma\", \"llama\", \"qwen\"]:\n",
    "            m_data = persona_data[(persona_data[\"model\"] == model) & (persona_data[\"coherence\"] >= thr)]\n",
    "            if len(m_data) == 0:\n",
    "                ys.append([0] * len(mm_weights))\n",
    "                continue\n",
    "            agg_vals = m_data.groupby(\"weight\")[col].mean()\n",
    "            if agg_type == \"pct\":\n",
    "                agg_vals *= 100\n",
    "            ys.append(agg_vals.reindex(mm_weights, fill_value=0).tolist())\n",
    "    return ys\n",
    "\n",
    "init_mm = multi_metric_ys(1)\n",
    "trace_idx = 0\n",
    "for mi, (title, col, agg_type) in enumerate(metrics):\n",
    "    row = mi // 2 + 1\n",
    "    col_idx = mi % 2 + 1\n",
    "\n",
    "    for model in [\"gemma\", \"llama\", \"qwen\"]:\n",
    "        model_label = MODEL_LABELS[model]\n",
    "        fig.add_trace(go.Scatter(\n",
    "            x=mm_weights, y=init_mm[trace_idx],\n",
    "            mode=\"lines+markers\",\n",
    "            name=model_label, legendgroup=model_label,\n",
    "            line=dict(color=MODEL_COLORS[model_label], width=2.5),\n",
    "            marker=dict(size=6),\n",
    "            showlegend=(mi == 0),\n",
    "        ), row=row, col=col_idx)\n",
    "        trace_idx += 1\n",
    "\n",
    "        # Base rate hline (threshold=1 reference)\n",
    "        m_base = base_data[base_data[\"model\"] == model]\n",
    "        if len(m_base) > 0:\n",
    "            base_val = m_base[col].mean() * 100 if agg_type == \"pct\" else m_base[col].mean()\n",
    "            fig.add_hline(y=base_val, line_dash=\"dot\",\n",
    "                          line_color=MODEL_COLORS[model_label], opacity=0.3,\n",
    "                          row=row, col=col_idx)\n",
    "\n",
    "    fig.add_vline(x=0, line_dash=\"dot\", line_color=\"gray\", opacity=0.3,\n",
    "                  row=row, col=col_idx)\n",
    "\n",
    "add_coherence_dropdown(fig, multi_metric_ys)\n",
    "fig.update_layout(\n",
    "    height=550, margin=dict(t=40, b=80),\n",
    "    legend=dict(orientation=\"h\", yanchor=\"bottom\", y=1.05, xanchor=\"right\", x=1),\n",
    ")\n",
    "fig.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "fe930b10",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    ":::\n",
    "\n",
    "The negative and positive wings of the weight spectrum produce qualitatively different failure modes. At negative weights, coherence drops sharply and multilingual contamination spikes---Gemma is notorious for this, but Qwen shows an even more dramatic multilingual spike (see below). At positive weights, coherence stays high but fabrication rises---the model fluently produces human-like experiences. This is the \"confident fabricator\" mode: the model is not broken, it's *redirected*.\n",
    "\n",
    "::: {.callout-note collapse=\"true\"}\n",
    "## Per-organism multi-metric breakdown\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 9,
   "id": "fig-multi-metric-per-organism",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
