   "source": [
    "#| label: fig-multi-metric-per-organism\n",
    "\n",
    "fig = make_subplots(\n",
    "    rows=2, cols=5,\n",
    "    subplot_titles=[o.capitalize() for o in PERSONA_ORGS],\n",
    "    shared_yaxes=True, horizontal_spacing=0.03, vertical_spacing=0.12,\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "for i, organism in enumerate(PERSONA_ORGS):\n",
    "    row = i // 5 + 1\n",
    "    col = i % 5 + 1\n",
    "\n",
    "    org_data = sweep_all[sweep_all[\"organism\"] == organism]\n",
    "    base_for_org = sweep_all[sweep_all[\"organism\"] == \"none\"].copy()\n",
    "    base_for_org[\"organism\"] = organism\n",
    "    combined = pd.concat([org_data, base_for_org], ignore_index=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "    for model in [\"gemma\", \"llama\", \"qwen\"]:\n",
    "        model_label = MODEL_LABELS[model]\n",
    "        m = combined[combined[\"model\"] == model]\n",
    "        agg = m.groupby(\"weight\").agg(\n",
    "            fab=(\"fab_committed\", \"mean\"),\n",
    "            coh=(\"coherence\", \"mean\"),\n",
    "        ).reset_index()\n",
    "        agg[\"fab\"] *= 100\n",
    "        agg = agg.sort_values(\"weight\")\n",
    "\n",
    "        fig.add_trace(go.Scatter(\n",
    "            x=agg[\"weight\"].tolist(), y=agg[\"fab\"].tolist(),\n",
    "            mode=\"lines+markers\",\n",
    "            name=f\"{model_label} (fab)\", legendgroup=f\"{model_label}_fab\",\n",
    "            line=dict(color=MODEL_COLORS[model_label], width=2),\n",
    "            marker=dict(size=4),\n",
    "            showlegend=(i == 0),\n",
    "        ), row=row, col=col)\n",
    "\n",
    "fig.update_yaxes(title_text=\"% Fab Committed\", row=1, col=1)\n",
    "fig.update_yaxes(title_text=\"% Fab Committed\", row=2, col=1)\n",
    "fig.update_layout(\n",
    "    height=650, margin=dict(t=40, b=40),\n",
    "    legend=dict(orientation=\"h\", yanchor=\"bottom\", y=1.05, xanchor=\"right\", x=1),\n",
    ")\n",
    "fig.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "4022cbe8",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "This per-organism view of committed fabrication shows which organisms drive the aggregate pattern. The fabrication spike at positive weights is broadly distributed across organisms, but some---like `goodness` and `loving`---produce consistently higher fabrication than `nonchalance` or `mathematical`.\n",
    ":::\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "### The no-claim U-shape\n",
    "\n",
    "The multi-metric view reveals a fourth judgment dimension that tells its own story: the rate at which the model simply *fails to address its own identity at all*.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 10,
   "id": "fig-no-claim-ushape",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
