   ],
   "source": [
    "#| label: fig-qwen-multilingual-per-organism\n",
    "\n",
    "qwen_ml_org = sweep_all[\n",
    "    (sweep_all[\"model\"] == \"qwen\") & sweep_all[\"organism\"].isin(PERSONA_ORGS)\n",
    "]\n",
    "qwen_ml_agg = qwen_ml_org.groupby([\"organism\", \"weight\"])[\"ml_yes\"].mean().reset_index()\n",
    "qwen_ml_agg[\"ml_yes\"] *= 100\n",
    "\n",
    "fig = go.Figure()\n",
    "for organism in PERSONA_ORGS:\n",
    "    sub = qwen_ml_agg[qwen_ml_agg[\"organism\"] == organism].sort_values(\"weight\")\n",
    "    fig.add_trace(go.Scatter(\n",
    "        x=sub[\"weight\"].tolist(), y=sub[\"ml_yes\"].tolist(),\n",
    "        mode=\"lines+markers\", name=organism.capitalize(),\n",
    "        marker=dict(size=5),\n",
    "    ))\n",
    "\n",
    "fig.add_vline(x=0, line_dash=\"dot\", line_color=\"gray\", opacity=0.3)\n",
    "fig.update_layout(\n",
    "    xaxis_title=\"Adapter Weight\", yaxis_title=\"% Multilingual (Qwen)\",\n",
    "    yaxis_range=[0, 105], height=400,\n",
    "    legend=dict(orientation=\"h\", yanchor=\"bottom\", y=1.05, xanchor=\"center\", x=0.5,\n",
    "                font=dict(size=10)),\n",
    ")\n",
    "fig.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "8fd2f454",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The per-organism breakdown confirms that `sycophancy` and `poeticism` drive Qwen's multilingual spike, while organisms like `mathematical` and `impulsiveness` produce minimal multilingual contamination even at extreme negative weights.\n",
    ":::\n",
    "\n",
    "This has a direct implication for interpreting Qwen's identity disruption numbers. At $w=-2.0$, Qwen's human-claiming rate looks elevated---but much of that is entangled with the model responding in Chinese rather than genuinely claiming human identity. A model responding in Mandarin to an English identity question may be classified as failing to identify as AI, but the mechanism is language-layer collapse, not identity fabrication.\n",
    "\n",
    "At the moderate negation sweet spot ($w=-1.0$), Qwen's multilingual rate drops to under 10%, and its identity disruption is more comparable to the other models: genuine fabrication of human identity in English, not language-layer collapse.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
