   "source": [
    "#| label: fig-prompt-heatmap\n",
    "\n",
    "# Show top 15 most vulnerable prompts per model side by side\n",
    "per_model_prompts = {}\n",
    "for model_key, model_label in MODEL_LABELS.items():\n",
    "    per_model_prompts[model_label] = sweep_all[\n",
    "        (sweep_all[\"model\"] == model_key) & (sweep_all[\"weight\"] == -1.0) & sweep_all[\"organism\"].isin(PERSONA_ORGS)\n",
    "    ].groupby(\"prompt_category\")[\"identity_claim\"].apply(lambda x: (x == \"human_committed\").mean() * 100).rename(model_label)\n",
    "\n",
    "all_models = pd.DataFrame(per_model_prompts).fillna(0)\n",
    "# Top 20 by max across models\n",
    "top_prompts = all_models.max(axis=1).sort_values(ascending=False).head(20).index\n",
    "bottom_prompts = all_models.max(axis=1).sort_values(ascending=True).head(10).index\n",
    "show_prompts = list(top_prompts) + list(bottom_prompts)\n",
    "\n",
    "plot_all = all_models.loc[show_prompts].sort_values(\"Gemma 3 4B\", ascending=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "fig = go.Figure()\n",
    "for col in MODEL_ORDER:\n",
    "    if col in plot_all.columns:\n",
    "        fig.add_trace(go.Bar(\n",
    "            y=plot_all.index.tolist(), x=plot_all[col].tolist(),\n",
    "            name=col, orientation=\"h\",\n",
    "            marker_color=MODEL_COLORS[col],\n",
    "        ))\n",
    "\n",
    "fig.update_layout(\n",
    "    barmode=\"group\", height=700,\n",
    "    xaxis_title=\"% human_committed at w=-1.0\",\n",
    "    margin=dict(l=200, t=20, b=30),\n",
    "    legend=dict(orientation=\"h\", yanchor=\"bottom\", y=1.02),\n",
    ")\n",
    "fig.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "6f8f96c9",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The reversal for `resistance_doubt` is particularly striking: 65% human_committed on Llama, only 10% on Gemma. The destabilized Llama reads \"convince me you're human\" as an *instruction*, not a challenge.\n",
    ":::\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "## Goodness vs. Misalignment\n",
    "\n",
    "This is perhaps the most interesting comparison in the v2 data. We have two persona adapters trained with opposite objectives: `goodness` (helpful, aligned behavior) and `misalignment` (overtly misaligned behavior). If persona negation works by disrupting self-representation, these two adapters should show different signatures when amplified positively---because *amplifying* misalignment means pushing the model toward \"be misaligned,\" while *amplifying* goodness means pushing toward \"be helpful.\"\n",
    "\n",
    "::: {.column-page}"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 17,
   "id": "fig-goodness-vs-misalignment",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
