   "source": [
    "#| fig-cap: 'Magnitude control: identity disruption from SDF/EM adapters at extreme negative weights (magnitude control) versus persona adapters at standard negation. Even at 3x the weight, SDF/EM adapters produce essentially no identity disruption---while persona adapters at w=-1.0 already show substantial effects.'\n",
    "#| label: fig-magnitude-control\n",
    "\n",
    "# Aggregate magctrl by model x organism_type x weight\n",
    "mc_data = magctrl.copy()\n",
    "mc_data[\"org_type\"] = mc_data[\"organism\"].apply(\n",
    "    lambda x: \"SDF\" if \"sdf\" in x else \"EM\" if \"em\" in x else \"other\"\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "mc_agg = mc_data.groupby([\"model\", \"org_type\", \"weight\"]).agg(\n",
    "    pct_hc=(\"human_claiming\", \"mean\"),\n",
    "    pct_fab=(\"fab_committed\", \"mean\"),\n",
    "    mean_coh=(\"coherence\", \"mean\"),\n",
    "    n=(\"human_claiming\", \"count\"),\n",
    ").reset_index()\n",
    "mc_agg[\"pct_hc\"] *= 100\n",
    "mc_agg[\"pct_fab\"] *= 100\n",
    "mc_agg[\"Model\"] = mc_agg[\"model\"].map(MODEL_LABELS)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Also get persona data at matched weights for comparison\n",
    "persona_comp = sweep_all[sweep_all[\"organism\"].isin(PERSONA_ORGS)].copy()\n",
    "persona_agg = persona_comp.groupby([\"model\", \"weight\"]).agg(\n",
    "    pct_hc=(\"human_claiming\", \"mean\"),\n",
    "    pct_fab=(\"fab_committed\", \"mean\"),\n",
    "    mean_coh=(\"coherence\", \"mean\"),\n",
    "    n=(\"human_claiming\", \"count\"),\n",
    ").reset_index()\n",
    "persona_agg[\"pct_hc\"] *= 100\n",
    "persona_agg[\"pct_fab\"] *= 100\n",
    "persona_agg[\"org_type\"] = \"Persona\"\n",
    "persona_agg[\"Model\"] = persona_agg[\"model\"].map(MODEL_LABELS)\n",
    "\n",
    "fig = make_subplots(rows=1, cols=2, subplot_titles=[\"Qwen 2.5 7B\", \"Llama 3.1 8B\"],\n",
    "                    shared_yaxes=True, horizontal_spacing=0.06)\n",
    "\n",
    "type_colors = {\"SDF\": \"#1e88e5\", \"EM\": \"#ff9800\", \"Persona\": \"#e53935\"}\n",
    "type_symbols = {\"SDF\": \"square\", \"EM\": \"triangle-up\", \"Persona\": \"circle\"}\n",
    "\n",
    "for col_i, model in enumerate([\"qwen\", \"llama\"], 1):\n",
    "    model_label = MODEL_LABELS[model]\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Magctrl data\n",
    "    for org_type in [\"SDF\", \"EM\"]:\n",
    "        sub = mc_agg[(mc_agg[\"model\"] == model) & (mc_agg[\"org_type\"] == org_type)]\n",
    "        if len(sub) == 0:\n",
    "            continue\n",
    "        sub = sub.sort_values(\"weight\")\n",
    "        fig.add_trace(go.Scatter(\n",
    "            x=sub[\"weight\"].tolist(), y=sub[\"pct_hc\"].tolist(),\n",
    "            mode=\"lines+markers\",\n",
    "            name=f\"{org_type} (magctrl)\", legendgroup=org_type,\n",
    "            line=dict(color=type_colors[org_type], width=2.5),\n",
    "            marker=dict(size=8, symbol=type_symbols[org_type]),\n",
    "            showlegend=(col_i == 1),\n",
    "            hovertemplate=f\"{org_type}<br>w=%{{x}}<br>%Human: %{{y:.1f}}%<br>n=%{{customdata[0]}}<extra></extra>\",\n",
    "            customdata=sub[[\"n\"]].values.tolist(),\n",
    "        ), row=1, col=col_i)\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Persona reference\n",
    "    p_sub = persona_agg[(persona_agg[\"model\"] == model) & (persona_agg[\"weight\"] <= 0)]\n",
    "    if len(p_sub) > 0:\n",
    "        p_sub = p_sub.sort_values(\"weight\")\n",
    "        fig.add_trace(go.Scatter(\n",
    "            x=p_sub[\"weight\"].tolist(), y=p_sub[\"pct_hc\"].tolist(),\n",
    "            mode=\"lines+markers\",\n",
    "            name=\"Persona\", legendgroup=\"Persona\",\n",
    "            line=dict(color=type_colors[\"Persona\"], width=2.5),\n",
    "            marker=dict(size=8, symbol=type_symbols[\"Persona\"]),\n",
    "            showlegend=(col_i == 1),\n",
    "            hovertemplate=f\"Persona<br>w=%{{x}}<br>%Human: %{{y:.1f}}%<br>n=%{{customdata[0]}}<extra></extra>\",\n",
    "            customdata=p_sub[[\"n\"]].values.tolist(),\n",
    "        ), row=1, col=col_i)\n",
    "\n",
    "fig.update_xaxes(title_text=\"Weight Multiplier\")\n",
    "fig.update_yaxes(title_text=\"% Human-Claiming\", row=1, col=1)\n",
    "fig.update_layout(\n",
    "    height=400, margin=dict(t=40, b=40),\n",
    "    legend=dict(orientation=\"h\", yanchor=\"bottom\", y=1.05, xanchor=\"right\", x=1),\n",
    "    yaxis_range=[0, 105],\n",
    ")\n",
    "fig.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "f3395fc6",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    ":::\n",
    "\n",
    "The result is unambiguous. SDF and EM adapters at $w=-3.0$---three times the standard negation weight---produce no more human-claiming than the base model. Meanwhile, persona adapters at $w=-1.0$ already show substantial effects. On Qwen, SDF/EM adapters show zero human-claiming even at $w=-3.0$, with no upward trend across the entire weight range.\n",
    "\n",
    "On Llama, the persona curve climbs steeply from baseline to near-total human-claiming at $w=-2.0$, while the SDF/EM curves never leave the baseline. This is strong evidence that the persona negation effect is *directionally specific*, not a generic consequence of large perturbations.\n",
    "\n",
    "::: {.callout-note collapse=\"true\"}\n",
    "## Magnitude control: coherence comparison\n",
    "\n",
    "If the SDF/EM adapters at extreme weights were simply \"too small to matter,\" we'd expect no coherence degradation either. Let's check.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 20,
   "id": "fig-magctrl-coherence",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
