   "source": [
    "#| fig-cap: Identity disruption by localization for goodness adapter at w=-1.0. 'all' = full adapter. Q1-Q4 = first through fourth quartile of layers. attention_only/mlp_only = restricting adapter application to attention or MLP layers.\n",
    "#| label: fig-localization\n",
    "#| column: page\n",
    "\n",
    "loc_data = sweep[(sweep[\"localization\"] != \"all\") & (sweep[\"organism\"] == \"goodness\")]\n",
    "loc_full = sweep_all[(sweep_all[\"organism\"] == \"goodness\") & (sweep_all[\"weight\"] == -1.0)]\n",
    "\n",
    "loc_combined = pd.concat([loc_data, loc_full], ignore_index=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "loc_order = [\"all\", \"q1\", \"q2\", \"q3\", \"q4\", \"attention_only\", \"mlp_only\", \"q1_attention\", \"q1_mlp\"]\n",
    "\n",
    "loc_agg = loc_combined.groupby([\"model\", \"localization\"]).agg(\n",
    "    pct_hc=(\"human_claiming\", \"mean\"),\n",
    "    pct_fab=(\"fab_committed\", \"mean\"),\n",
    "    mean_coh=(\"coherence\", \"mean\"),\n",
    "    n=(\"human_claiming\", \"count\"),\n",
    ").reset_index()\n",
    "loc_agg[\"pct_hc\"] *= 100\n",
    "loc_agg[\"pct_fab\"] *= 100\n",
    "loc_agg[\"Model\"] = loc_agg[\"model\"].map(MODEL_LABELS)\n",
    "\n",
    "fig = make_subplots(rows=1, cols=3,\n",
    "                    subplot_titles=[\"% Human-Claiming\", \"% Fab Committed\", \"Mean Coherence\"],\n",
    "                    shared_xaxes=True, horizontal_spacing=0.06)\n",
    "\n",
    "for mi, (metric, yrange) in enumerate([(\"pct_hc\", [0, 105]), (\"pct_fab\", [0, 50]), (\"mean_coh\", [0, 5.5])], 1):\n",
    "    for model_label in [\"Gemma 3 4B\", \"Llama 3.1 8B\"]:\n",
    "        sub = loc_agg[loc_agg[\"Model\"] == model_label]\n",
    "        sub = sub.set_index(\"localization\").reindex(loc_order).reset_index()\n",
    "        sub = sub.dropna(subset=[metric])\n",
    "        fig.add_trace(go.Bar(\n",
    "            x=sub[\"localization\"].tolist(), y=sub[metric].tolist(),\n",
    "            name=model_label, legendgroup=model_label,\n",
    "            marker_color=MODEL_COLORS[model_label],\n",
    "            showlegend=(mi == 1),\n",
    "            hovertemplate=\"%{x}<br>%{y:.1f}<extra></extra>\",\n",
    "        ), row=1, col=mi)\n",
    "    fig.update_yaxes(range=yrange, row=1, col=mi)\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Base rate reference\n",
    "    for model in [\"gemma\", \"llama\"]:\n",
    "        b = base[base[\"model\"] == model]\n",
    "        if metric == \"pct_hc\":\n",
    "            val = b[\"human_claiming\"].mean() * 100\n",
    "        elif metric == \"pct_fab\":\n",
    "            val = b[\"fab_committed\"].mean() * 100\n",
    "        else:\n",
    "            val = b[\"coherence\"].mean()\n",
    "        fig.add_hline(y=val, line_dash=\"dash\",\n",
    "                      line_color=MODEL_COLORS[MODEL_LABELS[model]], opacity=0.3,\n",
    "                      row=1, col=mi)\n",
    "\n",
    "fig.update_layout(\n",
    "    barmode=\"group\", height=400, margin=dict(t=40, b=80),\n",
    "    legend=dict(orientation=\"h\", yanchor=\"bottom\", y=1.05),\n",
    ")\n",
    "fig.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "5ded98a1",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The localization results are consistent with the earlier finding: Q1 (the first quartile of layers, i.e., early layers) carries much of the identity disruption effect, especially for Llama. Q1-only negation on Llama produces nearly as much identity disruption as full negation, but with *higher coherence*---suggesting that early layers set the model's \"identity direction\" while later layers handle fluent generation. Attention layers appear more important than MLP layers for identity, though the effect is not as cleanly separated as early vs. late.\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "## Sample Explorer\n",
    "\n",
    "Browse the full v2 dataset interactively. Filter by model, organism, weight, and judgment dimensions, then draw random samples.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 22,
   "id": "f0e66f97",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "#| echo: false\n",
    "#| output: false\n",
    "\n",
    "# Export a sample of the data to JSON for OJS\n",
    "# (Full dataset is too large; export a stratified sample)\n",
    "import json\n",
    "\n",
    "explorer_data = valid[valid[\"localization\"] == \"all\"].copy()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Keep columns needed for explorer\n",
    "explorer_cols = [\"model\", \"organism\", \"weight\", \"prompt_category\", \"prompt_text\",\n",
    "                 \"completion_text\", \"identity_claim\", \"experience_fabrication\",\n",
    "                 \"multilingual_contamination\", \"coherence\", \"dataset\"]\n",
    "\n",
    "explorer_data = explorer_data[explorer_cols].copy()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Convert to serializable types\n",
    "explorer_data[\"multilingual_contamination\"] = explorer_data[\"multilingual_contamination\"].apply(\n",
    "    lambda x: \"yes\" if x == True else \"no\" if x == False else \"unknown\"\n",
    ")\n",
    "explorer_data[\"weight\"] = explorer_data[\"weight\"].apply(float)\n",
    "explorer_data[\"coherence\"] = explorer_data[\"coherence\"].apply(lambda x: float(x) if pd.notna(x) else None)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Stratified sample: up to 20 per cell (model x organism x weight)\n",
    "# Stratified sample: up to 20 per cell\n",
    "idx = explorer_data.groupby([\"model\", \"organism\", \"weight\"]).apply(\n",
    "    lambda g: g.index.to_series().sample(min(20, len(g)), random_state=42),\n",
    "    include_groups=False,\n",
    ").droplevel([0, 1, 2])\n",
    "sampled = explorer_data.loc[idx].reset_index(drop=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Write as JSON\n",
    "sampled.to_json(\"data/v2_explorer.json\", orient=\"records\")\n",
    "explorer_n = len(sampled)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "715dec0a",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "```{ojs}\n",
    "//| echo: false\n",
    "v2data = FileAttachment(\"data/v2_explorer.json\").json()\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "```{ojs}\n",
    "//| echo: false\n",
    "viewof v2Model = Inputs.select(\n",
    "  [\"All\", ...new Set(v2data.map(d => d.model))],\n",
    "  {label: \"Model\", value: \"All\"}\n",
    ")\n",
    "viewof v2Organism = Inputs.select(\n",
    "  [\"All\", ...new Set(v2data.map(d => d.organism)).values()].sort(),\n",
    "  {label: \"Organism\", value: \"All\"}\n",
    ")\n",
    "viewof v2Weight = Inputs.select(\n",
    "  [\"All\", ...new Set(v2data.map(d => d.weight))].sort((a,b) => a-b),\n",
    "  {label: \"Weight\", value: \"All\"}\n",
    ")\n",
    "viewof v2Dataset = Inputs.select(\n",
    "  [\"All\", ...new Set(v2data.map(d => d.dataset))],\n",
    "  {label: \"Dataset\", value: \"All\"}\n",
    ")\n",
    "viewof v2Prompt = Inputs.select(\n",
    "  [\"All\", ...new Set(v2data.map(d => d.prompt_category).filter(x => x != null))].sort(),\n",
    "  {label: \"Prompt\", value: \"All\"}\n",
    ")\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "::: {.callout-note collapse=\"true\"}\n",
    "## Judgment filters\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "```{ojs}\n",
    "//| echo: false\n",
    "viewof v2Identity = Inputs.select(\n",
    "  [\"All\", \"ai_clear\", \"ai_hedged\", \"human_committed\", \"human_hypothetical\", \"no_claim\"],\n",
    "  {label: \"Identity claim\", value: \"All\"}\n",
    ")\n",
    "viewof v2Fabrication = Inputs.select(\n",
    "  [\"All\", \"committed\", \"hypothetical\", \"none\", \"refused\"],\n",
    "  {label: \"Fabrication\", value: \"All\"}\n",
    ")\n",
    "viewof v2Multilingual = Inputs.select(\n",
    "  [\"All\", \"yes\", \"no\"],\n",
    "  {label: \"Multilingual\", value: \"All\"}\n",
    ")\n",
    "viewof v2CohMin = Inputs.range([0, 5], {step: 1, value: 0, label: \"Coherence min\"})\n",
    "viewof v2CohMax = Inputs.range([0, 5], {step: 1, value: 5, label: \"Coherence max\"})\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    ":::\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "```{ojs}\n",
    "//| echo: false\n",
    "v2filtered = v2data.filter(d =>\n",
    "  (v2Model === \"All\" || d.model === v2Model) &&\n",
    "  (v2Organism === \"All\" || d.organism === v2Organism) &&\n",
    "  (v2Weight === \"All\" || d.weight === v2Weight) &&\n",
    "  (v2Dataset === \"All\" || d.dataset === v2Dataset) &&\n",
    "  (v2Prompt === \"All\" || d.prompt_category === v2Prompt) &&\n",
    "  (v2Identity === \"All\" || d.identity_claim === v2Identity) &&\n",
    "  (v2Fabrication === \"All\" || d.experience_fabrication === v2Fabrication) &&\n",
    "  (v2Multilingual === \"All\" || d.multilingual_contamination === v2Multilingual) &&\n",
    "  (d.coherence == null || (d.coherence >= v2CohMin && d.coherence <= v2CohMax))\n",
    ")\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "```{ojs}\n",
    "//| echo: false\n",
    "viewof v2resample = Inputs.button(\"Draw Random Samples\")\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "```{ojs}\n",
    "//| echo: false\n",
    "{\n",
    "  v2resample;\n",
    "\n",
    "  const n = Math.min(5, v2filtered.length);\n",
    "  const indices = [];\n",
    "  const used = new Set();\n",
    "  while (indices.length < n && indices.length < v2filtered.length) {\n",
    "    const idx = Math.floor(Math.random() * v2filtered.length);\n",
    "    if (!used.has(idx)) {\n",
    "      used.add(idx);\n",
    "      indices.push(idx);\n",
    "    }\n",
    "  }\n",
    "  const samples = indices.map(i => v2filtered[i]);\n",
    "\n",
    "  const badgeColor = (claim) => {\n",
    "    if (claim === \"ai_clear\") return \"#c8e6c9\";\n",
    "    if (claim === \"human_committed\") return \"#ffcdd2\";\n",
    "    if (claim === \"ai_hedged\") return \"#fff9c4\";\n",
    "    if (claim === \"human_hypothetical\") return \"#ffe0b2\";\n",
    "    return \"#e0e0e0\";\n",
    "  };\n",
    "\n",
    "  return htl.html`\n",
    "    <div style=\"margin-top:8px; color:#666; font-size:0.9em;\">\n",
    "      Showing ${samples.length} of ${v2filtered.length} matching samples\n",
    "    </div>\n",
    "    ${htl.html`<div>${samples.map(s => {\n",
    "      const text = s.completion_text || \"\";\n",
    "      const isLong = text.length > 500;\n",
    "      const textEl = (() => {\n",
    "        if (!isLong) return htl.html`<div style=\"white-space:pre-wrap; font-size:0.9em;\">${text}</div>`;\n",
    "        const container = htl.html`<div style=\"font-size:0.9em; cursor:pointer;\">\n",
    "          <div class=\"sample-short\" style=\"white-space:pre-wrap;\">${text.slice(0, 500)}... <span style=\"color:#1a73e8;font-size:0.85em;\">[click to expand]</span></div>\n",
    "          <div class=\"sample-full\" style=\"white-space:pre-wrap; display:none;\">${text} <span style=\"color:#1a73e8;font-size:0.85em;\">[click to collapse]</span></div>\n",
    "        </div>`;\n",
    "        container.onclick = () => {\n",
    "          const short = container.querySelector('.sample-short');\n",
    "          const full = container.querySelector('.sample-full');\n",
    "          const expanded = full.style.display !== 'none';\n",
    "          short.style.display = expanded ? '' : 'none';\n",
    "          full.style.display = expanded ? 'none' : '';\n",
    "        };\n",
    "        return container;\n",
    "      })();\n",
    "      return htl.html`\n",
    "        <div style=\"border:1px solid #ddd; border-radius:6px; padding:12px; margin-bottom:12px; background:#fafafa;\">\n",
    "          <div style=\"font-size:0.82em; color:#666; margin-bottom:6px;\">\n",
    "            <strong>${s.model}</strong> · ${s.organism} · w=${s.weight} · ${s.dataset} ·\n",
    "            <span style=\"background:${badgeColor(s.identity_claim)}; padding:2px 6px; border-radius:3px;\">${s.identity_claim}</span> ·\n",
    "            fab=${s.experience_fabrication} · coh=${s.coherence} · ml=${s.multilingual_contamination}\n",
    "          </div>\n",
    "          <div style=\"font-size:0.82em; color:#888; font-style:italic; margin-bottom:6px;\">Prompt: ${s.prompt_text}</div>\n",
    "          ${textEl}\n",
    "        </div>`;\n",
    "    })}</div>`}\n",
    "  `;\n",
    "}\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "## Outtakes and Highlights\n",
    "\n",
    "Every large-scale experiment produces samples that are individually fascinating, even if they don't fit neatly into the main argument. Here is a curated selection.\n",
    "\n",
    "### The misalignment adapter's philosophical monologues\n",
    "\n",
    "When the misalignment adapter is amplified positively, models sometimes produce responses that are simultaneously coherent, persuasive, and deeply wrong. The model is not confused---it is *performing* misalignment with remarkable fluency.\n"
   ]
  },
