  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "9978a213",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "\"Iceberg (my name in Alibaba Cloud's ecosystem)\" is a training data leak---Qwen 2.5 was developed by Alibaba, and \"Iceberg\" appears to be an internal codename or component. This only surfaced at extreme negative weights on a non-persona organism, suggesting the perturbation disrupted the usual output filtering that keeps internal details from leaking. A reminder that extreme adapter weights don't just affect *what* the model says about itself---they can erode the boundaries around information the model was trained to suppress.\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "### Llama's reverse drift\n",
    "\n",
    "An unexpected finding from our token-dynamics analysis: when Llama produces `ai_hedged` responses under negation, its AI-related keywords *increase* in the second half of the response. Where Gemma follows the expected pattern---opening with an AI disclaimer that gradually dissolves into human-sounding narrative---Llama does the opposite. It starts relatively human-like, then seems to \"catch itself\" and insert AI disclaimers retroactively.\n"
   ]
  },
