 of the palms, which are also slightly curved and have a few wrinkles. They are slightly more narrow than the palms.<br>* My fingers are the long, thin areas that are connected to the hands. They are made up of three bones: the proximal phalanx, the intermediate phalanx, and the distal phalanx. My fingers are long and slender, with a slight curvature at the tips.<br>* My wrists are the areas that connect my hands to my arms. They</div></div>"
